{
  "texts": [
    "To answer our second research question, we sought to abstract the legal process to discern whether jurors made different decisions when presented with legal allegations and factual scenarios written by ChatGPT versus those written by human lawyers.",
    "We explored this using real-world securities class action cases.",
    "In order to more fulsomely evaluate ChatGPT's legal drafting skills, we included cases of varying quality.",
    "We wanted to evaluate ChatGPT's drafting ability not only for high quality cases (i.e., those a judge decided had merit to continue through the legal process), but also those of lower quality (i.e., that a judge dismissed).",
    "We used class action cases because, overwhelmingly, cases brought by the SEC are successful: in 2022, for example, it won 12 of its 15 trials (U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission 2022)."
  ]
}